defaultIt is essential that RHR continues its work of guaranteeing Palestinian farmers access to their property
default. 
defaultLetting lands lie fallow leads to their takeover
default either by settlers from settlements adjacent to these lands o
defaultr by the State
default. Ottoman law, still 
defaultapplicable
default in Area C, states that uninterrupted cultivation of land for a period of ten years, without objections from any party, grants the farmer rights to the land. In absence of such rights, the land reverts to the 
defaultS
defaultt
defaultate. 
defaultIt is critical, therefore, that l
defaultandowners continue 
defaultto 
defaultwork their lands not only to allow them to continue to subsist from their produce, but to ensure its ongoing ownership. 
